---

Trim the ends from the @spring onion{2} then finely slice.

Chop the @baby corn{60%g} in half.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and stir-fry until starting to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add half the spring onion and the baby corn and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @Panang curry paste{50%g} and @Thai garnish{1}(chopped) (don't use all of it, it's hot!) and cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @coconut milk{200%ml} and @sugar snap peas{150%g} and simmer with the lid on (or some foil) until thick and the chicken is cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat up the @steamed basmati rice{1%pouch} - squeeze the pouch, tear the strip and microwave at 800W for ~{2%minutes}. Or stir-fry the rice for ~{3%minutes} in a dry frying pan over a medium-high heat.

Taste your curry and add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{} if needed.

Serve the rice in #bowls{} topped with the chicken Panang and a sprinkling of the remaining spring onion. ENJOY!